    • main

      public static void main​(java.lang.String[] args)
      Main function. Provides console interface for Implementor class. Runs in two modes depending on count of arguments args:
      1. 2 arguments - className outputPath creates .java file by executing Impler method implement(Class, Path)
      2. 3 arguments - -jar className jarOutputPath creates .jar file by executing JarImpler method implementJar(Class, Path)
      If argument count isn't equal to 3 or 4 then method throws ImplerException
      Parameters:
      args - command line arguments.
